  "texts": [
    "Enforcing a desired postsynaptic pattern density is equivalent to adjusting an activity threshold.",
    "At CA3, two encodings for each image converge: x MF μν with density 0.02 and x PP μν with density 0.2.",
    "Not only are MF patterns sparser, they are less correlated with average correlation 0.01, compared to a corresponding value of 0.09 for PP patterns.",
    "Such an association between sparsification and decorrelation has been widely reported across many theoretical models and brain regions [10] [11] [12] [13], and it is also captured by our model.",
    "Decreasing postsynaptic pattern density (sparsification) correspondingly decreases the postsynaptic correlation (decorrelation) for any presynaptic statistics (Fig. 2E)."
  ],
